    url: "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Izfp0CD_Da0",
    docUrl: "https://www.westonwi.gov/AgendaCenter/ViewFile/Agenda/_03232026-1898",
    isAgendaOnly: false,
    badge: "new",
    overview: "The Village of Weston Board of Trustees approved multiple rezoning ordinances, modified a speed limit ordinance for Weston Avenue after debate, and received updates on the April 2026 referendum for fire department funding. The board also approved a 10-year baseball\/softball field maintenance agreement and deferred action on remote meeting attendance policy to the next meeting when newly elected officials will be seated.",
    agenda: [
      { time:"0:00", item:"Call to order and Pledge of Allegiance" },
      { time:"0:45", item:"Roll call" },
      { time:"1:15", item:"Public comments" },
      { time:"5:30", item:"Minutes from previous meeting - February 16th" },
      { time:"6:00", item:"Acknowledge reports from boards, committees, and commissions" },
      { time:"7:00", item:"Department reports (Administrator, Clerk, Finance, Fire\/EMS, Parks\/Rec, Planning, Police, Public Works, Technology)" },
      { time:"22:00", item:"Consent agenda - Vouchers and appointment of agent change" },
      { time:"24:00", item:"Ordinances - Rezoning and speed limit changes" },
      { time:"35:00", item:"Resolution - Final plat of Hinter Springs Second Edition" },
      { time:"36:00", item:"Referendum informational sessions update" },
      { time:"40:00", item:"New business items including parking restrictions, intersection signage, field agreements" },
    ],
    discussions: [
      { item:"Public Comment - Fire Department Funding", body:"Jim Pensel of 5002 Aerrol Street spoke passionately about SAFER fire department staffing issues after attending the citizen academy. He criticized the board's approach of using referendums instead of prioritizing fire department funding in the budget, arguing spending on artificial turf and the aquatic center are 'wants' while fire\/EMS is a 'need.' He called on the board to 'stop looking for the easy way out through referendums and start making the hard choices.'" },
      { item:"Finance Director Response to Public Comment", body:"Finance Director Jessica responded that the village cannot borrow for additional firefighters - only operating revenue can fund them, which is why a referendum is needed. She noted the turf at Kennedy Park was funded through approved borrowing, not operating funds. She expressed frustration with criticism, noting the village is 'the cheapest' and 'most efficient' but cannot continue without more revenue, and suggested her position may be open in a couple months." },
      { item:"Ordinance 26-00006 - Speed Limits on Weston Avenue", body:"Significant debate occurred over the proposed 35 mph speed limit on Weston Avenue from Von Kennel to Ryan Street. Trustee Maloney argued the road is too good and wide for 35 mph compared to other village roads. The original motion to approve failed 4-3 with Maloney, Jordan, and the President voting no. An amended motion by Maloney was approved changing Von Kennel to Highway J back to 45 mph while keeping Camp Phillips to Von Kennel at 35 mph." },
      { item:"Intersection Signage at Community Center Drive and Birch Street", body:"Motion to change stop sign to yield sign was amended after Trustee Hooang raised safety concerns about bicyclists coming off the pedestrian bridge at 15-20 mph with no signage requiring them to stop. A friendly amendment was accepted to add a stop sign for bicyclists on the path. Motion passed unanimously as amended." },
      { item:"Baseball\/Softball Field Maintenance Agreement", body:"The board approved a 10-year agreement with youth baseball and softball organizations for field maintenance at Kennedy Park. Parks staff explained the long term protects the village's investment and provides stability despite leadership changes in organizations. The agreement requires organizations to maintain fields in lieu of fees. Passed unanimously." },
      { item:"Remote Meeting Attendance Policy", body:"Trustee Lewis recommended postponing this item until the next meeting so the newly seated board can make the decision. Motion to defer passed unanimously." },
      { item:"Microsoft Teams for Trustee Communication", body:"Board approved using Microsoft Teams for trustee communication starting next term to replace text messaging between trustees. Staff will provide training for new board members. Passed unanimously." },
    ],
    publicComment: "Jim Pensel of 5002 Aerrol Street spoke about fire department staffing, criticizing the referendum approach and calling for budget reprioritization to fully fund SAFER. He attended the department's inaugural citizen academy and emphasized the exhaustion and understaffing he witnessed.",
